      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>579 threads, <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=0>1</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=25>2</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=50>3</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=75>4</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=100>5</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=125>6</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=150>7</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=175>8</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=200>9</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=225>10</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=250>11</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=275>12</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=300>13</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=325>14</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=350>15</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=375>16</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=400>17</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=425>18</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=450>19</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=475>20</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=500>21</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=525>22</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=550>23</a> <a href=classes.html?class=11&start=575>24</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=classes.html?class=11&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96873231629346></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96873231629346><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Wizards and AOE spells</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1471><span id=Sage>Cryselle</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>35 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 12th 12:18 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I figured that since I havn't seen any AOE spell posts, I'd open this can of worms myself. <br><br>Lets face it, some people love them, others hate them, but AOE spells are undoubtably one of the most difficult spell lines in a wizard's arsenal to pull off without getting your butt handed to you. Part of this is that there are a lot of misconceptions, both on the part of the wizards and on those they group with. I'm going to give my personal opinions and a few strategies to go with the various lines of spells, but I hope to see other people helping identify good and bad sides to them all as well.<br><br>General Misconceptions<br><br>1) Can't stress this one enough. Centering an AOE spell on your tank does not fool MOBS into thinking that the tank cast it. Sorry. No dice. <br><br>2) Your groups enchanter will mez them off you, so it's safe. Sorry. AOEs and Chanters mix /extremely/ well, but only if you have people who know exactly what they are doing (see below). In almost all situations, it's better just to shelve the AOEs and just play it straight. You annoy less people that way.<br><br>3) Here's a plus one. Unless you're PvP, your AOE spells are not going to hit your groupmates. You can toast yourself with them, but everyone else is safe. :)<br><br>4) If used in a dungeon, it will pull a huge train. The correction to this is that it /may/ pull a huge train, if you use it in the wrong places. The key is to know what is above and below you. Some places, like Unrest, LGuk, Kedge, CT, have a lot of places that are layered on top of each other. Don't use them here. Others, like SolB (my favorite) and most outdoor zones, have very few locations. If you don't know, don't use them.<br><br>On to specific lines<br><br>Al'Kabor series: (Anything Spiral of Al'Kabor, these are easy to identify)<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;        Pros: It can hit a lot of opponents.<br><br>         Cons: High mana, low damage, all those opponents get mad at you and beat you into a bloody pulp. Honestly, as much as I love AOE spells, but I have never been in a situation where these spells were actually more helpful than harmful. Hope someone else can help me on this one.<br><br>Tight AOEs (Column of frost, pillar of fire, circle of force, etc)<br><br>         Pros: These, used well, are quite useful. If I'm in AOE mode, this is the line I'll use on 3-4 opponents. Trick to using these is to center it on the opponent the tanks are fighting. Then cast like you would a DD spell. If you don't taunt the prime one on you, even for a split second, then you very very rarely taunt the others on. <br><br>         Cons: If you fire it off too quickly, you will taunt the whole group of bad guys on you. And, while it is slightly better damage to mana than most DDs, you really need to decide if it is worth the extra risk.<br><br>Caster Centered AOEs (Numbing Cold, Fingers of Fire, Project Lightning, Supernova, etc)<br><br>         Pros: The fastest casting AOEs, and you don't have to worry about hitting yourself with them. These, when combined with the enchanter color flux series, can be used to take down huge trains quickly. Or get you killed. It requires a lot of set up, and a good working knowledge of what you're fighting. Best against large numbers of low blues, because a few resists can turn win to loss in a heartbeat. Have to admit that it is very fun though. (My favorite use of these is when farming bandit sashes to fix qeynos guard faction, which I wreck all the time. Sit down in the middle of a small camp, watch them all get mad at you, then lash out with project lightning and watch the camp go poof)<br><br>         Cons: Only hits things in melee range of you,  and lets face it, do you really want to be in melee range of a large number of opponents?<br><br>Rains (Rain of Anything, Anything Storm)<br><br>       Pros: Used right, these can really dish it out. Using Frost Storm in the CR of SolB on 2 opponents, I was turning 312 mana into 1000 damage (500 to each). Comparing to the 180 mana for 405 damage of Lightning Shock (Conflag was out, fire based in SolB is resisted too often) and you can see why I liked it. Rain spells strike 3 times on 1 opponent, 2 times on 2 opponents, and once only if it hits 3 or 4. So to max damage with it, use it on 2 or 4 opponents.<br>I like it best on 2 opponents, because the tank will usually keep the attention of one, and I can park the other out of the fight for later. <br><br>     Cons: It's really, really, really easy to walk into this one, especially if you're casting it on 1 or 2 opponents. Forget that it pulses more than once and walk in, just to see it rip a bubble off your HP. Whoops.<br><br><br>Anyhow, that's what I can think of for now.<br><br><br>Cryselle Silverwynd<br>Hell 45 wizardess<br>Tribunal<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
